    "updated_at": "2015-06-19T23:28:42Z",
    "body": "It looks like panics are turned into aborts on the boundaries of functions with non-Rust ABI.\nBut it should probably be documented anyway.\n\n```\nextern \"Rust\" fn Rust() -> ! {\n    panic!();\n}\nextern \"C\" fn C() -> ! {\n    panic!();\n}\n\nstruct S;\nimpl Drop for S {\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\n        println!(\"Drop!\");\n    }\n}\n\nfn main()\n{\n    let _s = S;\n    //Rust(); // Drop!\n    C(); // No Drop!\n}\n```\n",
